  "prompt": "How do I filter out US election news in my Quora feed?",
  "response": "To filter out US election news from your Quora feed, you can try several approaches:\n\n1. **Mute Topics**: \n   - Go to the topic pages related to US elections, such as \"US Elections,\" \"Presidential Elections,\" \"United States Politics,\" etc.\n   - Click on the three dots or the settings icon on the topic page and choose \"Mute topic.\" This will reduce the visibility of questions and answers related to those topics in your feed.\n\n2. **Adjust Interests**:\n   - Navigate to your Quora profile settings and review your interests.\n   - Remove or adjust interests related to politics or elections to receive less content focused on these areas.\n\n3. **Hide Specific Questions**: \n   - When you come across a question in your feed related to US elections, click on the \"\u2026\" (three dots) next to the question.\n   - Select \"Not Interested\" or \"Hide this question\" to reduce similar content in your feed.\n\n4. **Follow Non-Political Topics**: \n   - Follow more topics unrelated to politics or elections that interest you. This will help diversify your feed with content that is more aligned with your preferences.\n\n5. **Customize Email and Notification Settings**:\n   - Check your email preferences and push notifications in your settings to reduce updates on topics you\u2019re not interested in.\n\nThese steps should help you tailor your Quora feed to fit your interests and reduce exposure to unwanted US election news.",
